Department of Agriculture
mission_statement: To serve all Americans by providing effective, innovative, science-based public policy leadership in agriculture, food and nutrition, natural resource protection and management, rural development, and related issues with a commitment to deliver equitable and climate-smart opportunities that inspire and help America thrive.

name: Department of Commerce
mission_statement: Create the conditions for economic growth and opportunity for all communities.

name: Department of Defense
mission_statement: Provide the military forces needed to deter war and ensure our nation's security.

name: Department of Defense Office of Inspector General
Department of Education
mission_statement: Promote student achievement and preparation for global competitiveness by fostering educational excellence and ensuring equal access.

name: Department of Homeland Security
mission_statement: With honor and integrity, we will safeguard the American people, our homeland and our values.

name: Department of Housing and Urban Development
mission_statement: Create strong, sustainable, inclusive communities and quality affordable homes for all. HUD is working to strengthen the housing market to bolster the economy and protect consumers; meet the need for quality affordable rental homes; utilize housing as a platform for improving quality of life; build inclusive and sustainable communities free from discrimination; and transform the way HUD does business.

name: Department of Labor
mission_statement: To foster, promote, and develop the welfare of the wage earners, job seekers, and retirees of the United States; improve working conditions; advance opportunities for profitable employment; and assure work-related benefits and rights.

name: Department of State
mission_statement: To protect and promote U.S. security, prosperity, and democratic values and shape an international environment in which all Americans can thrive.

name: Department of Transportation
mission_statement: To deliver the world’s leading transportation system, serving the American people and economy through the safe, efficient, sustainable, and equitable movement of people and goods.

name: Department of Veterans Affairs
mission_statement: To fulfill President Lincoln's promise, “To care for him who shall have borne the battle and for his widow and his orphan”.

name: Department of the Interior
mission_statement: Protect and manage the Nation’s natural resources and cultural heritage; provide scientific and other information about those resources; and honor its trust responsibilities or special commitments to American Indians, Alaska Natives, Native Hawaiians, and affiliated Island Communities.

name: Environmental Protection Agency
mission_statement: To Protect Human Health and the Environment

name: General Services Administration
mission_statement: To deliver the best customer experience and value in real estate, acquisition, and technology services to the Government and the American people.

National Aeronautics and Space Administration
mission_statement: NASA explores the unknown in air and space, innovates for the benefit of humanity, and inspires the world through discovery.

name: National Institute of Standards and Technology
National Science Foundation
mission_statement: To promote the progress of science; to advance the national health, prosperity, and welfare; and to secure the national defense.

name: Office of Personnel Management
mission_statement: We are champions of talent for the Federal Government. We lead Federal agencies in workforce policies, programs, and benefits in service to the American people.

Office of the U.S. Trade Representative
Small Business Administration
mission_statement: Maintain and strengthen the nation’s economy by enabling the establishment and vitality of small businesses and by assisting in the economic recovery of communities after disasters.

name: Social Security Administration
mission_statement: Ensure equity and accessibility in delivering Social Security services by improving the customer experience and addressing systemic barriers to participation in our programs.

name: U.S. Department of Health & Human Services
mission_statement: Enhance the health and well-being of all Americans, by providing for effective health and human services and by fostering sound, sustained advances in the sciences underlying medicine, public health, and social services.

name: U.S. Department of Justice
mission_statement: To uphold the rule of law, to keep our country safe, and to protect civil rights.

name: U.S. Department of the Treasury
mission_statement: Maintain a strong economy and create economic and job opportunities by promoting the conditions that enable economic growth and stability at home and abroad, strengthen national security by combating threats and protecting the integrity of the financial system, and manage the U.S. Government’s finances and resources effectively.

name: United States Agency for International Development
mission_statement: We work to build a freer, more equitable and more humane world by amplifying local voices, advancing sustainable progress, and tackling the world's toughest problems.

name: United States Nuclear Regulatory Commission
mission_statement: The NRC licenses and regulates the Nation’s civilian use of radioactive materials, to provide reasonable assurance of adequate protection of public health and safety, to promote the common defense and security, and to protect the environment.
